article.headline: Akron 123, Denison 52
article.story: AKRON, Ohio (AP) -- Bubba Walther had 21 points in 19 minutes, and six other Akron players scored in double figures Wednesday night as the Zips routed Division III Denison 123-52. Zach Sowers scored 12 points and Matt Futch had 11 for the Zips, who shot 59.7 percent from the floor while holding the Big Red (2-7) to 33.9 percent shooting. The Zips (3-1) used 14 players, with no one playing more minutes than Walther. Robb Hern led Denison with 16 points and Jordan Krantz had 13. Akron connected on 19 of 31 shots from 3-point range while Denison was 2-for-12 beyond the arc. Akron outrebounded Denison 46-29 and scored 37 points off 25 turnovers. Nick Dials, Dru Joyce, Romeo Travis and John Ryback each scored 10 points for Akron.
